I want to share what has gone on with Newton in hopes to help others who are corgi owners, and the many other breeds that back/spinal issues more commonly occur too. Newton was on crate rest for a disc in his spine that had some mineralization. This sometimes can be treated with lots of crate rest and medicine management. This includes a muscle relaxer and steroids for Newton. Once the dose was decreased was when things declined quickly so it was only masking the injury. In less than 24 hours, Newton was unable to walk on his own. I rushed him to ER Saturday morning and he was evaluated and he was still able to walk somewhat so we kept resting. But later that day he was no longer able to walk at all and we were back at ER. A pain med was added and we needed to see a neurologist. I was hoping they'd be open on Monday the 3rd, so I talked to my primary vet (referrals are required) and then called the Neurologist. They asked for a video of him trying to walk... called me within 10 minutes of sending the video saying the doctor wanted to see him right now. I took him to the Neurologist and he needed an MRI and surgery that day. My sweet boy was in surgery for 4 hours because the the disc was much worse. The biggest test was to see how he was Tuesday morning. The strength of his reflexes would tell us if he could walk again and make a full recovery.

Tuesday morning came, and my boy was thriving!! His reflexes were strong on both legs and the doctor was thrilled! He was moved from IV meds to oral meds and hopefully able to bring him home Wednesday. Wednesday morning came around and doc called... HE CAN WALK ON HIS OWN!! She was so happy with his progress and told me she wished all her patients did as well as Newton! I could bring my baby home. I picked him up and he walked into the room on his own to see me. I instantly cried. He will make a full recovery. We have lots of rest and physical therapy ahead but as you all know, anything for my Newton. I want to share this because of all those who love my boy, and to bring awareness to this. I’ll be sharing his recovery journey with you! We appreciate all the love and support! ❤️
